<!--- Don't mess with this line! --->{{Unreviewed|date=October 2013}}

In [[rhetoric]], '''brevitas''' is a style and [[figure of thought]]  that uses the minimum amount of words to express an idea.<ref>{{cite web|title=Changing Minds: Brevitas|url=http://changingminds.org/techniques/language/figures_speech/brevitas.htm}}</ref> It connotes expression without gloss and artifice, similar to but more problematic than ''puritas'', one of the classical virtues of speech.<ref>{{cite book | url=http://books.google.com/books?id=8iL0uoNEJXUC&pg=PA231&dq=brevitas&hl=en&sa=X&ei=c21vUqnEC8vxkQeWs4Bw&ved=0CF4Q6AEwCQ#v=onepage&q=brevitas&f=false | title=The Visible World: Samuel Van Hoogstraten's Art Theory and the Legitimation of Painting in the Dutch Golden Age | publisher=Amsterdam University Press | author=Thijs Weststeijn | year=2008 | pages=231<U+2013>234}}</ref> It is often associated with an [[ellipsis (linguistics)|elliptic linguistic style]].<ref>{{cite book | url=http://books.google.com/books?id=xuTr6BbY9MoC&pg=PA188&lpg=PA188&dq=brevitas+rhetoric+definition&source=bl&ots=xVM92gRiVM&sig=Z38yM2a6w9GJw5-wjd6B-KEVuPM&hl=en&sa=X&ei=_WhvUojlCs-lkQel0YDgAQ&ved=0CFoQ6AEwBzgK#v=onepage&q=brevitas&f=false | title=Literary Rhetoric: Concepts - Structures - Analyses | publisher=[[Brill Publishers]] | author=Heinrich F. Plett | year=2010 | pages=188}}</ref>

==Brevitas in Rhetoric==

[[Rhetorica ad Herennium]], a text attributed to [[Cicero]] but whose author is unknown, defines brevitas as "the expressing of an idea by the very minimum of essential words."<ref>{{cite book|last=Blacketer|title=The School of God: Pedagogy and Rhetoric in Calvin's Interpretation of Deuteronomy|year=2006|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=pTxlFyS3f4cC&pg=PA71&lpg=PA71&dq=the+expressing+of+an+idea+by+the+very+minimum+of+essential+words+Rhetorica+ad+Herennium,+1954.&source=bl&ots=N0F11sGjm7&sig=ojmo8zJC9VZSKuoEiYlef5-kX5M&hl=en&sa=X&ei=zktlUoidEZbK4AP_qIGoAw&ved=0CCwQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=the%20expressing%20of%20an%20idea%20by%20the%20very%20minimum%20of%20essential%20words%20Rhetorica%20ad%20Herennium&f=false}}</ref>  This does not mean that brevitas lacks rhetorical [[Amplification (rhetoric)|amplification]], but expresses it in another style of rhetoric.

==Examples of Brevitas==
* Looking good!
* It is what it is
* Life happens
* It is well with my soul
* Such is life

